author: app.com
title: Johnson puts Jackson Memorial football past TR South
text:
MORE JACKSON - No starting quarterback, no problem for the Jackson Memorial High School football team Friday night.
Senior Kyle Johnson took charge with big plays on both sides, sparking the Jaguars past visiting Toms River South 28-7 and into the driver’s seat for a Central Group IV playoff berth.
With junior passer Dan Barker sidelined by a concussion, Johnson caught a 58-yard touchdown and returned an interception 50 yards for a score as the Jaguars (4-3) snapped a three-game losing streak. Toms River South (4-2) had shut out three of its first five opponents.
“Kyle is a great athlete,” sophomore quarterback A.J. Tolmachewich said. “He’s always around the ball, flying on every play.”
Exhibit A: With Jackson leading 7-0 late in the first quarter, Tolmachewich executed a nice play-action fake and hit an open Johnson in stride at Toms River South’s 20. The senior changed gears as he got under the ball and took it in from there.
